{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"33d87922-560e-4fa6-887a-12960c5fdf86","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the TFM:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run `dotnet restore` and `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any NuGet packages that need updated versions for .NET 11 compatibility (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1d94e4b5-a68e-445f-b11b-6fd3c37e4cd9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no tools needed.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the three files they mentioned.","outputTokens":276,"requestId":"D000:634EC:1872B9D:1BDAB51:69E821CF"},"id":"1d1deb57-b013-4673-a322-ed53532645df","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:18:13.009Z","parentId":"2e004083-5821-40d0-aa3b-d682d822d383"}
